# ==============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS FOR TEAMS (when moving to organization)
# ==============================================================================
#
# When moving to a GitHub organization, replace @drgaciw with team names:
#
# 1. Create teams in GitHub organization (Settings â†’ Teams)
# 2. Replace individual username with @your-org/team-name format
# 3. Example teams:
#    - @your-org/engineering (all engineers)
#    - @your-org/tech-leads (technical leadership)
#    - @your-org/ai-team (AI/ML engineers)
#    - @your-org/regression-approvers (authorized to approve AI regressions)
#    - @your-org/devops (DevOps team)
#    - @your-org/security (security team)
# 4. Enable "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection rules
# 5. Test by creating a PR that modifies files with different owners
#
# Example team-based configuration:
#   /packages/ai/** @your-org/ai-team @your-org/tech-leads
#   /.github/workflows/ @your-org/devops @your-org/tech-leads
#
# ==============================================================================
